    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-04-16T12:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-04-16T12:30:00-05:00" n="454"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d454">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">352.3715/43: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Valencia</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-16T13:00:00-04:30"
                            >April 16, 1937—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 16—11:55 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>589. Department’s 310, April 15, 6 p.m.<note n="62" xml:id="d454fn62">Not
                        printed.</note> The Cuban Embassy states this morning that it has
                    encountered difficulties on the part of the Spanish Government in its efforts to
                    evacuate its refugees, but that it hopes to be able to give us a definite
                    statement tomorrow or the next day.</p>
                <p>I fear that the Cuban Embassy will not have its refugees ready for embarkation
                    for another week or 10 days, and would suggest that the Department proceed with
                    its plans concerning Malaga transfers. The departure of the Cubans from Madrid
                    can be made contingent upon our readiness to receive them at Alicante.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
